It can not be a scam if you didn't end up having any gain from said project. In fact, he most likely lost money for this project. So despite both sentences: "Logan is the creator and frontman of the Cryptozoo project" AND "Cryptozoo is a scam" are factually correct and indisputable. It still is not correct to say that Logan scammed people with Cryptozoo. Because that implies it was Logan to actually scam people, which is also factually wrong when we previously established the two concepts above.
